column33: I think when an AI makes a mistake it's a result of a 'hallucination'. What I mean by that is that the AI simply attempts to answer my question in a way that aligns with what it perceives as a natural response based on training data without any foundation for the information.
column41: ChatGPT is a language learning model that takes data from the internet and uses it to inform how it should speak or answer questions. You can think of it as analogous to the way a person would create text but in place of real life experience is training data.
column42: It collects data from many unique sources. This data is supplemented by information gleaned from user input and web search capabilities.
column54: Dall-E uses your text along with its training data to de-noise an image with bias. It essentially 'sculpts' a series of pixels randomly based on input and seed.
